context: <b8_0>Architecture<b8_0/> (Latin architectura, from the <a1_0>Greek<a1_0/> ἀρχιτέκτων <b6_0>arkhitekton<b6_0/> "architect", from <a2_0>ἀρχι- "<b7_0>chief<b7_0/>" and τέκτων "builder"<a2_0/>) is both the process and the product of planning, designing, and constructing <a3_0>buildings and other physical structures<a3_0/>. <a0_0><b9_0>Architectural<a0_0/> works<b9_0/>, in the material form of buildings, are often perceived as cultural symbols and <a4_0>as works of art<a4_0/>. <a5_0>Historical civilizations<a5_0/> are often identified with their surviving <b10_0>architectural achievements<b10_0/>.
